icians: Violin - Katie Lander, Amy Heggart, Pippa Jameson-Evans, Vincent Spencer, Jane Miller, Graham Clarke, Jon Kwan, Satoko. Viola - Zoltan Abbott, Cassandra Hodgson, Amy Hoskens, Benedict Taylor. Cello - Richard Thomas, Laura Seddon, Billy Key, Maria Roduiguez. Double Bass - Edgar Smith. Flute - Nicholas Sabisky, Soraya Momeni. Bass Clarinet - Robert Fish, Elliot Devivo. Trumpet - John Eacott, Peter Rolinson. French Horn - Dave Lawrence. Trombone - Ashley Slater, Andy Robinson. Marimba - Greta Eacott, Merlin Jones. Vibraphone - Rosa Lynch, Tayra Fuentes. Voice - Fiona Hymns, Ciara Burrows, Andrew Smith, John Vallance. Taiko Drums - Yoshinori Hayashi, Shun Sato. Jazz Drums - Moses Boyd. Jazz Trumpet - Mark Kaicuma. Jazz Sax - Ruben Fox.<br />\r\nFilm:Tom Pollock<br />\r\nSound: Benjamin Davies<br />\r\nProject co-ordinator: Natasha Bird<br />\r\nFloodtide: John Eacott'),(14,'Floodtide by Wolf Pack',64086220,NULL,NULL,'2014-04-09 14:35:33','2014-04-09 14:35:33',640,480,'435458933_640.jpg',56838,'image/jpeg',640,512,1,61,'Floodtide was performed by contemporary music collective Wolf Pack as part of their eighth concert \'Tide\' at Chisenhale Dance Space in East London.  Data used was calculated from the Thames tide at London Bridge.'),(15,'Floodtide at the Roundhouse',66049809,NULL,NULL,'2014-04-09 14:35:39','2014-04-09 14:35:39',640,480,'437301633_640.jpg',39324,'image/jpeg',640,426,1,132,'Floodtide was performed at the Dorfman Hub, The Roundhouse on 10th May 2013 as part of the Accidental Festival.  A sensor at Trinity Buoy Wharf, Docklands, read tidal data which was transformed into notation sung by workshop participants.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nPerformers:<br />\r\nAna Maio, Ciara Burrows, Lucy Hooberman, Thomas Brennan, Milda Samsonaite, Rory Mernagh, Hua Tan, Andrew Walsh, Peter Gordon, Emmett Glynn, Iris Ederer, Bethan Mascarenhas, Toril Briese.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nLyrics for this performance are taken from Paul Francis\' illustrated story, Tidalism.<br />\r\nFloodtide is created by John Eacott.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nhttp://www.floodtide.eu/events/floodtide-at-accidental-festival'),(16,'Floodtide Open',76169433,NULL,NULL,'2014-04-09 14:35:46','2014-04-09 14:35:46',640,480,'450908059_640.jpg',45525,'image/jpeg',640,426,1,127,'Musicians gathered under Blackfriars Rail Bridge to play musical notation generated by the tidal flow of the Thames.'),(17,'Floodtide Open at the National Maritime Museum',81378722,NULL,NULL,'2014-04-09 14:35:53','2014-04-09 14:35:53',640,478,'457498803_640.jpg',53431,'image/jpeg',640,426,1,74,'Part of Lost at Sea Late, an event to mark the opening of NMM\'s exhibition Turner and the Sea.  Musicians gathered  to play music generated from the tide. A sensor at Trinity Buoy Wharf gathers data which is transformed live into notation.'),(18,'Floodtide Thames Daiku rehearsal',91940693,NULL,NULL,'2014-04-22 09:48:39','2014-04-22 09:48:55',1280,720,'471498106_640.jpg',41760,'image/jpeg',640,360,1,109,'Workshop rehearsal of Floodtide with the Thames Daiku directed by Joji Hirota. Playing rhythms determined by live tide data. Survival Studios, Acton, London 13.4.2014'),(19,'Floodtide brass workshop in the garden',92139354,NULL,NULL,'2014-04-22 09:49:16','2014-04-22 09:49:16',1280,720,'471775354_640.jpg',59867,'image/jpeg',640,360,1,153,'Live sonification performance of Floodtide using notation generated from the Thames Tide. Stockwell, London'),(20,'Floodtide at Trinity Buoy Wharf',104927022,NULL,NULL,'2014-09-01 16:25:36','2014-09-01 16:25:52',1280,720,'487593193_640.jpg',63738,'image/jpeg',640,360,1,96,'19th April 2014. <br />\nFloodtide by John Eacott - music determined by tidal flow. A sensor submerged in the Thames at Trinity Buoy Wharf, Docklands, reads tidal flow which is transformed live into notation for musicians to play. See music being generated live at http://floodtide.eu/play<br />\nLaunch of the Floodtide Listening post - a mechanical music machine playing music determined by the tide of the Thames.  Machine by Andrew Baldwin, music by John Eacott.<br />\nPerformance by Dulwich Folk Choir and Joji Hirota\'s Thames Daiku.'),(21,'Dulwich Folk Choir sing Floodtide',104930685,NULL,NULL,'2014-09-01 16:26:38','2014-09-01 16:26:38',640,360,'487597065_640.jpg',54434,'image/jpeg',640,360,1,96,'19th April 2014.<br />\nFloodtide is a musical performance by John Eacott that is determined by tidal flow.<br />\nA sensor submerged in the Thames at Trinity Buoy Wharf reads tidal flow data which is transformed into notation and read from screens by musicians. <br />\nHere, Dulwich Folk Choir sing sections of traditional Orkney folk songs that are arranged according to the movement of the tide.'),(22,'Thames Daiku play Floodtide',104932855,NULL,NULL,'2014-09-01 16:27:00','2014-09-01 16:27:00',640,360,'487598900_640.jpg',63350,'image/jpeg',640,360,1,80,'19th April 2014.<br />\nFloodtide is a musical performance by John Eacott that is determined by tidal flow.<br />\nA sensor submerged in the Thames at Trinity Buoy Wharf reads tidal flow data which is transformed into notation and read from screens by musicians. <br />\nHere, Joji Hirota\'s Thames Daiku play rhythms determined by the movement of the tide.'),(23,'Floodtide Worldwide Greenwich',104929350,NULL,NULL,'2014-09-01 16:27:30','2014-09-01 16:27:30',640,360,'487595155_640.jpg',35350,'image/jpeg',640,360,1,73,'Floodtide at the National Maritime Museum, Greenwich,  20th and 21st April 2014.<br />\n<br />\nFloodtide Worldwide was a series of live and Skyped performances from around the world to celebrate Floodtide notation being permanently available online at http://floodtide.eu/play<br />\n<br />\nMusicians from London, Leeds, Northamptonshire (UK) and Boston (USA) live broadcast performances of Floodtide over Skype. Ensembles including Wolfpack, JE Brass 5 and MA_ensemble performed live at the National Maritime Museum, Greenwich.'),(24,'Floodtide Jazz demo',109250738,NULL,NULL,'2014-10-18 14:28:10','2014-10-18 14:28:10',640,4